Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:08.170
As the auto industry evolves,

00:00:08.170 --> 00:00:12.290
so do the technologies that drive the
vehicles of the future. Hybrid electric

00:00:12.290 --> 00:00:14.360
vehicles are making a noticeable impact,

00:00:14.360 --> 00:00:17.470
and we're proud to say that we are
developing state-of-the-art testers for

00:00:17.470 --> 00:00:18.180
this market.

00:00:18.180 --> 00:00:23.230
D&amp;V electronics has gained global
recognition for developing highly

00:00:23.230 --> 00:00:25.460
advanced testers for development,

00:00:25.460 --> 00:00:30.099
performance and production testing of
hybrid and electric motor and inverters.

00:00:30.099 --> 00:00:34.690
The EPT Series encompasses three core
principles:

00:00:34.690 --> 00:00:39.850
Advanced technology, Modularity and Real-Time
Data Analysis.

00:00:39.850 --> 00:00:43.510
Our research and development department
has made major breakthroughs

00:00:43.510 --> 00:00:46.989
in developing proprietary technology
to test electric motors

00:00:46.989 --> 00:00:51.149
and inverters. Our technology innovations
have been in power measurement, battery simulation

00:00:51.149 --> 00:00:56.070
and the real time analysis of critical
motor and inverter characteristics.

00:00:56.070 --> 00:00:59.620
Our test platforms are designed to
easily accommodate

00:00:59.620 --> 00:01:03.190
the complex variety of testing requirements
from Global OEM's

00:01:03.190 --> 00:01:08.119
and Tier-1s. D&amp;V's core technologies in
Power Supply and Motor Testing

00:01:08.119 --> 00:01:12.409
are integrated into every test system,
whether it be the production testing of

00:01:12.409 --> 00:01:13.880
hybrid electric motors,

00:01:13.880 --> 00:01:17.299
the laboratory testing of truck and bus
motors and inverters

00:01:17.299 --> 00:01:21.880
or the long term durability testing of
Belt and Integrated Starter Generators.

00:01:21.880 --> 00:01:25.649
Our testers provide the fastest method
of capturing real-time data.

00:01:25.649 --> 00:01:29.759
The internal tester components and
controllers from the PC

00:01:29.759 --> 00:01:33.680
are linked via a network connection for
high-speed data transfer

00:01:33.680 --> 00:01:37.009
via industrial Ethernet protocol called
EtherCat.

00:01:37.009 --> 00:01:40.490
This provides real-time performance data
processing

00:01:40.490 --> 00:01:46.200
in less than 25 microseconds.
The EPT series of testers

00:01:46.200 --> 00:01:50.680
provides the customer with a system that
allows end-to-end implementation

00:01:50.680 --> 00:01:57.240
from laboratory through endurance to
production. The EPT-150 system

00:01:57.240 --> 00:02:01.439
is a high-precision laboratory tester
for evaluating the performance of

00:02:01.439 --> 00:02:03.149
electric motors and inverters.

00:02:03.149 --> 00:02:08.920
The EPT-150 has been designed to support
the development of cutting-edge inverter

00:02:08.920 --> 00:02:12.750
e-motor system technologies. With high
acceleration,

00:02:12.750 --> 00:02:16.239
low inertia drive lines and significant
power capabilities,

00:02:16.239 --> 00:02:19.760
D&amp;V supplies innovative electric motor
systems

00:02:19.760 --> 00:02:23.870
up to 20,000 rpm. The power measurement
module

00:02:23.870 --> 00:02:27.220
is a technology that synchronously
samples all torque,

00:02:27.220 --> 00:02:33.659
power and speed inputs at a high sample
rate. The D&amp;V Test System Software suite

00:02:33.659 --> 00:02:38.030
includes an oscilloscope viewer to
investigate all high speed measurements

00:02:38.030 --> 00:02:41.400
with high resolution. The result is an
affordable,

00:02:41.400 --> 00:02:45.510
highly advanced turnkey system for
comprehensive evaluation

00:02:45.510 --> 00:02:52.310
have electric powertrain components.
The EPT-130 series of inverter/motor

00:02:52.310 --> 00:02:53.209
testers

00:02:53.209 --> 00:02:56.730
was built for the hybrid-electric belted
starter generator and

00:02:56.730 --> 00:03:01.200
integrated starter generator market.
The EPT-130

00:03:01.200 --> 00:03:05.269
is in addition to D&amp;V Electronics line
of durability testers

00:03:05.269 --> 00:03:08.540
developed as an endurance tester for
starter/generator

00:03:08.540 --> 00:03:13.590
belted and direct drive start-stop
systems. This specialized testing

00:03:13.590 --> 00:03:17.569
equipment can be utilized with multiple
start/stop architectures.

00:03:17.569 --> 00:03:22.230
Engineers have the ability to evaluate
and stress their newest starter

00:03:22.230 --> 00:03:25.390
or generator products during endurance
testing cycles.

00:03:25.390 --> 00:03:30.540
D&amp;V Electronics software will apply
customize drive cycle loading for

00:03:30.540 --> 00:03:32.489
hundreds of hours continuously.

00:03:32.489 --> 00:03:35.939
Multiple inverters, humidity thermal
chambers

00:03:35.939 --> 00:03:42.090
and cooling chiller systems can be
integrated into the tester system.

00:03:42.090 --> 00:03:43.569
The EPT-126

00:03:43.569 --> 00:03:47.849
is a high-volume motor tester able to
run fast test sequences

00:03:47.849 --> 00:03:51.480
with various start/stop motor
configurations including

00:03:51.480 --> 00:03:55.030
Integrated Starter generators and
Belted Starter Generators.

00:03:55.030 --> 00:04:00.079
There are multiple features that make
this tester an attractive offering.

00:04:00.079 --> 00:04:04.250
A soft-start retractable spline system
has been developed,

00:04:04.250 --> 00:04:08.230
which assists in protecting against
operator product damage.

00:04:08.230 --> 00:04:13.959
The EPT-126 production tester was
developed with a focus on low takt-time

00:04:13.959 --> 00:04:18.410
and user safety. The automated product
clapping assembly

00:04:18.410 --> 00:04:22.780
and a corresponding automated door system
with interlocking closure systems

00:04:22.780 --> 00:04:28.330
provides a high level of safety.
